          "type": "rtf",
          "settings": {
            "richtext_content": "<p>Ross Edgley is a world-renowned endurance athlete, author, and adventurer known for pushing the boundaries of human performance. With numerous world records under his belt, including being the first person to swim around Great Britain, Ross embodies the Gym King ethos of resilience, dedication, and breaking limits. As a proud Gym King ambassador, Ross inspires others to embrace challenges and pursue greatness in every aspect of life.</p>"
          }
        },
        "video_dx9fM3": {
          "type": "video",
          "settings": {
            "linked_video": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ETDJ44zMGeQ"
          }
        },
        "rtf_7bBxeU": {
          "type": "rtf",
          "settings": {
            "richtext_content": "<h3>Career Highlights</h3><p><strong>2015: Strongman Swimming<br/></strong>Completed a 100-kilometer swim while towing a 100-pound tree, blending strength and endurance in an unprecedented feat of physical and mental toughness.<strong><br/><br/>2016: Guinness World Record for Rope Climbing<br/></strong>Climbed the height of Mount Everest (8,848m) on a rope in just 19 hours, setting a Guinness World Record for rope climbing endurance.<br/><br/><strong>2016: Marathon While Pulling a Car</strong><br/>Ran a full 26.2-mile marathon while pulling a 1.4-ton car, proving his concept of “functional fitness” and redefining the boundaries of strength training.</p><p><strong>2018: First human to swim around the entire coastline of Great Britain</strong><br/>Ross Edgley made history by becoming the first person to swim around the entire coastline of Great Britain, an immense feat of endurance and determination. Over the course of 157 days, Ross swam 1,780 miles, battling unpredictable weather, strong currents, and physical exhaustion. He completed the swim without setting foot on land, a continuous six hours of swimming followed by six hours of rest aboard a support boat. An incredible feat of physical resilience which cemented his status as one of the world’s most remarkable endurance athletes.</p><p><strong>2024: World record holder of the longest non-stop river swim<br/></strong>Another history making record, Ross took on the longest non-stop river swim which took place on the Yukon river in Canada lasting a mammoth 54 hours and 45 minutes, Ross was not allowed to touch land or any boat to complete over 510KM of continuous swimming.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
